, 6.\n\nru _k_ , to shine: ro _k_ ate, I, 58, 2, &c.; rurukva\xc2\xb4n, I, 149, 3; su-ru _k_\na ru _k_ ana _h_ , III, 15, 6; ro _k_ ata, IV, 10, 6:1;--ati ro _k_ ase, thou\nshinest forth, I, 94, 7;--pra aro _k_ ayat, it filled with light, I, 143,\n2;--vi-ro _k_ amanam, I, 95, 2; 9; vi ro _k_ ase, II, 7, 4; vi-ruru _k_ u _h_\n, they have made shine, IV, 7, 1.\n\nru _g_ , to break: ru _g_ an, I, 71, 2; adrim ru _g_ ema, IV, 2, 15:3;--vi ru\n_g_ a, destroy, IV, 3, 14.\n\nRudra, a name of Agni, I, 27, 10:3; IV, 3, 1:1; rudram ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ a\xc2\xb4nam, p.\n467 III, 2, 5:1;--Rudra, the father of the Maruts, II, 1, 6; IV, 3, 6; 7; V,\n3, 3:2;--pl., the Rudras, I, 45, 1; 58, 3; III, 8, 8; 20, 5.\n\nRudriya, Rudra-like: rudriya, I, 72, 4:1;--pl., the sons of Rudra, III, 26, 5.\n\nrudh: vi rodhat, he grows up, I, 67, 9.\n\nrup: rupa _h_? IV, 5, 7:1; 8.\n\nru _s_ at, bright, brilliant, III, 29, 3; IV, 3, 9; 5, 15; 11, 1; V, 1,\n2;--red, IV, 7, 9.\n\nru _s_ at-urmi, with fiery waves, I, 58, 4:4.\n\nruh: vaya\xc2\xb4 _h_ -iva anu rohate, he mounts up as on the branches (of a tree),\nII, 5, 4:1.\n\nrupa, appearance, I, 71, 10; 95, 8; IV, 11, 1:2.\n\nreku, empty (?), IV, 5, 12:1.\n\nrek _n_ as, property, I, 31, 14.\n\nre _g_ , to tremble: are _g_ etam, I, 31, 3; re _g_ ante, they roll forward,\nI, 143, 3.\n\nretas, seed, sperm, I, 68, 8:1; 71, 8; 128, 3; reta _h_ (read repa _h_ ), IV,\n3, 7:2; diva _h_ na retasa, V, 17, 3:3.\n\nrepas, sin: repa _h_ (conj. for reta _h_ ), IV, 3, 7:2; stain, IV, 6, 6.\n\nrebha, singer, I, 127, 10:5.\n\nrevat, rich: reva\xc2\xb4n, I, 27, 12;--revat, with riches, I, 79, 5; 95, 11; II, 2,\n6; 9, 6; III, 7, 10; 18, 4; 5: 23, 2; 4; V, 23, 4.\n\nresha _n_ a, harm-doer, I, 148, 5.\n\nrai, wealth: ra\xc2\xb4ya _h_ , gen., I, 68, 10:1; ya\xc2\xb4sat raya\xc2\xb4 sa-ratham, I, 71,\n6:3; raya _h_ dura _h_ , I, 72, 8; raya _h_ su-dhura _h_ , I, 73, 10:1; raya\n_h_ _s_ i _s_ ihi, III, 16, 3:2.\n\nroka, shining light, III, 6, 7.\n\nro _k_ ana, light: vi _s_ va diva _h_ ro _k_ ana\xc2\xb4, I, 146, 1; III, 12, 9; diva\n_h_ ro _k_ ane, III, 6, 8; tri\xc2\xb4 ro _k_ ana\xc2\xb4ni, I, 149, 4; ut-tama _h_ ro _k_\nana\xc2\xb4nam, III, 5, 10; ro _k_ ane su\xc2\xb4ryasya, III, 22, 3.\n\nro _k_ ana-stha\xc2\xb4, dwelling in light, III, 2, 14.\n\nro _k_ is, splendour, V, 26, 1.\n\nrodasi, du., the two worlds, Heaven and Earth, I, 31, 3, &c.; I, 59, 2; 4:1;\nIII, 7, 9:2; V, 16, 4:3.\n\nrodhas, bank, IV, 5, 1:2.\n\nroman, hair, I, 65, 8.\n\nrohita, red (horses), I, 94, 10; II, 30, 2; III, 6, 6; IV, 2, 3; 6, 9.\n\nrohit-a _s_ va, lord of red horses, I, 45, 2; IV, 1, 8.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: L](sbe46161.htm)\n\n"